<HEAD>Stephen Sondheim Named Oxford Drama Professor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OXFORD, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stephen Sondheim, creator of musicals
including ``Sweeney Todd,'' ``Follies'' and ``Sunday in the Park
with George,'' will become the first visiting professor of drama
and musical theater at Oxford University.
   The university said Tuesday that the post was funded under a
$2.9 million endowment from Cameron Mackintosh, whose London
productions have included the hits ``Cats'' and ``Les Miserables.''
The fund will also be used to provide studio space for
undergraduates at Oxford.
   Sondheim will begin his six-month assignment in January, as a
fellow of St. Catherine's College. He will also conduct workshops
and master classes at institutions other than Oxford, the
university said.
