<HEAD>Heavy Rain in Parts of Texas, Other Areas of South</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A generous scattering of showers led to the posting today of
flood watches in parts of northeast Texas, and rain fell elsewhere
throughout the South.
   Showers and thunderstorms pelted parts of Texas as a result of
the remnants of Hurricane Chantal _ which was downgraded to a
tropical depression _ and locally heavy rain was expected to cause
flooding in the state.
   Showers and thunderstorms lingered this morning from Virginia
into northern Florida, across Tennessee, Alabama, Georgia, and from
northeast Texas across the upper Texas Gulf coast.
   Showers were scattered in the Texas Panhandle, New Mexico and
the Rockies, as well as northern Utah, and the northern Pacific
Coast.
   The nation's high temperature Tuesday was 112 degrees at
Bullhead City, Ariz.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms extending
from central and eastern Texas across southern Oklahoma, Louisiana,
Mississippi and Alabama, as well as from southern Florida across
southern South Carolina; scattered showers and thunderstorms in
Montana and central Colorado; rainshowers extending from northeast
New York state across northern New England.
   Predicted highs: 80s and 90s across much of the nation; 70s
across northern New England, from the northern Rockies to the
Pacific Northwest, and along the Pacific Coast; near 100 in western
North Dakota and eastern Montana; near 115 in the desert Southwest.
   The nation's temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 45 degrees
at McCall, Idaho, to 94 at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 77 cloudy; Boston 63 foggy; Buffalo 65 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 74 foggy; Cincinnati 71 hazy; Cleveland 62 fair;
Detroit 65 fair; Miami 83 fair; New York 66 fair; Philadelphia 67
partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 65 foggy; Portland, Maine, 61 foggy;
Washington 70 partly cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 82 windy; Chicago 73 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
80 windy; Denver 67 partly cloudy; Des Moines 69 fair; Indianapolis
68 foggy; Kansas City 71 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 73 fair;
Nashville 73 cloudy; New Orleans 79 fair; St. Louis 71 hazy.
   _West: Albuquerque 64 cloudy; Anchorage 57 rain; Las Vegas 85
fair; Los Angeles 66 fair; Phoenix 94 fair; Salt Lake City 83
partly cloudy; San Diego 67 fair; Seattle 60 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 70 partly cloudy; Toronto 68 partly cloudy.
