<HEAD>Six Children Die in Trailer Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONROE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six children were killed when fire swept
through their family's trailer home early today in a rural area of
northern Louisiana, firefighters said.
   Neighbors said the dead children ranged in age from 2 to 16.
   Their parents, Ronald and Mary Jane Ellerbe, were listed in fair
condition at E.A. Conway Memorial Hospital in Monroe, where they
were treated for smoke inhalation.
   Two other children _ Mary, 14, and Glen, 9 _ also survived and
were not injured, neighbors said.
   Neighbor Patsy Naron said she was awakened by Mrs. Ellerbe
banging on her door and screaming ``Fire.''
   ``We ran out and the farthest end of the trailer was on fire,''
said Ms. Naron's daughter, Denise, 17. ``You could hear the kids
screaming. The whole trailer was up in flames and the trees were on
fire.''
   She said she and others were ``trying to tell the kids to go to
the back (of the trailer). The front was all just on fire.''
   A Ouachita Parish Fire Department spokesman said Ms. Naron
reported the fire at 12:18 a.m. Firefighters had the fire under
control within five minutes of arriving, he said.
