<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--Popcorn-Scorpion     08-02 0103</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Popcorn-Scorpion,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Stung by Scorpion in Popcorn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANDY, Utah (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman eating popcorn out of a bowl she had
set down in her garage was stung in the mouth by a scorpion,
authorities say.
   Diane Bleckert, 56, was treated at Alta View Hospital and
released Tuesday, a nursing supervisor said.
   The scorpion, a species common to northern Utah that measures
about an inch, apparently crawled into the bowl, firefighter Val
Farnsworth said.
   Bleckert was stung on the inside of her lower lip before she bit
the scorpion in half, said a hospital spokeswoman who would not
give her name.
</TEXT>
