<HEAD>Aroma of Breakfast Leads to Arrest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOBILE, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An aroma of bacon and eggs led to the arrest
of the cook, who was at the stove but not in his own house.
   Sgt. Mike Barton said Mike Richardson, 25, was being sought by
Florida and Alabama state police on a stolen car charge when he
apparently left Interstate 10 for breakfast in Mobile early
Wednesday.
   Residents of the house called police when they awoke at 1:45
a.m., smelling breakfast.
   Richardson was treated for a hand injury he received when police
interrupted his breakfast. He was charged with burglary and assault.
   Richardson listed his address as 51 Government St., which is the
jail.
