<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--LostChecks     08-02 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Lost Checks,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Lights Back on for Ultility Customers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKE WORTH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Things looked dark for 300 Lake Worth
Utilities customers when the Postal Service lost nearly $40,000
worth of checks for electrical bills.
   But the Postal service put a little light back in the customers'
lives by finding the missing checks _ three weeks and hundreds of
angry phone calls later.
   Postal Service officials acknowledge ``a failure in the postal
system,'' but won't be more specific.
   The missing checks were worth $39,598.88. They were mailed June
23, promptly disappeared and then reappeared July 12.
   ``It's a shame it happened,'' Jerry Kindred, director of
marketing for the post office in West Palm Beach, said Tuesday.
``I'm sorry as all get-out about it.''
   Ten customers had their electricity cut off, said Brenda
Nedzweckas, business manager for the city-run utility. All 302
customers received late notices and electricity cutoff warnings.
All were billed an extra $10 in late charges, later waived.
</TEXT>
