<SECOND>AM-Hospital Escape,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mental Patient Escapes Hospital Following Similar Escape</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIDDLETOWN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A suicidal man escaped from a mental
hospital Wednesday, five days after another patient walked away
from the institution and stabbed a 9-year-old girl to death, police
said.
   Tim Stone, 24, slipped out of Connecticut Valley Mental Hospital
around 10:30 a.m., authorities said.
   Stone was not considered dangerous to others, but may harm
himself, police said.
   He was arrested July 21 in Wallingford on 1986 motor vehicle
charges and 1987 charges of burglary, larceny and criminal
mischief, said Wallingford police Sgt. Thomas Curran.
   Stone was committed to Connecticut Valley after trying to hang
himself in jail, Curran said. His last known address is Oakboro,
N.C.
   Last Friday, David Peterson, 37, walked away from the hospital
and took a bus to downtown Middletown, where dozens of people
watched in horror as he stabbed a 9-year-old girl to death at a
street fair.
   Hospital officials said Peterson was free to move about within
an unlocked, unguarded building. Hospital Superintendent Carl
Cappello did not immediately return telephone messages left with
his office.
