the government said.
   The Commerce Department said Tuesday that residential,
non-residential and government construction activity fell 0.8
percent in June to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of $414.7
billion, the lowest level since October. The decline followed a 0.6
percent gain in May and a 0.8 percent drop in April.
