<FIRST>r f PM-AT&amp;T-Ozone     08-02 0124</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AT&amp;T-Ozone,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>AT&amp;T To Eliminate CFCs From Manufacturing Processes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. says it
intends to eliminate by 1994 all emissions from its factories of a
chemical that destroys the ozone layer.
   AT&amp;T said Tuesday it was the first American electronics
manufacturer to set such a target for emissions of
chlorofluorocarbons.
   The company said it already has a policy of not accepting any
packaging from its suppliers that is made with chlorofluorocarbons.
It said it will work with all its suppliers to put the new policy
into place.
   AT&amp;T said it uses the chemicals in hundreds of manufacturing
processes. It said it intends to cut emissions in half from 1986
levels by 1991 as an interim step.
</TEXT>
