<HEAD>Infiniti Sedan Pegged at $38,000</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nissan Motor Corp. says it will price its
Infiniti Q45 luxury sedan at $38,000, putting it in a league with
Toyota Motor Corp.'s Lexus luxury car and just below Europe's most
expensive luxury sedans.
   The Infiniti Q45 is a four-door sedan, equipped with a 4.5
liter, 32-valve, 278-horsepower V8 engine. Its two-door coupe, with
a 3-liter, 162-horsepower V6, will be priced at $23,500, the
company said Tuesday.
   Prices cover all options including leather interior, sunroof,
premium stereo system, anti-lock brakes and automatic temperature
control, said Bill Bruce, Infiniti vice president and general
manager.
   The Infinitis will appear in showrooms Nov. 8.
   Toyota's V8-powered Lexus LS400 four-door luxury sedan is
scheduled for public introduction Sept. 1. It will be priced at
$35,000.
   ``They'll be priced right on each other and slightly below their
German competition,'' said Charles Brady, automotive analyst for
Oppenheimer &amp; Co. Inc. in New York. ``I think it's a real test for
the Japanese, to see if anybody wants to pay that much for a
Japanese car.''
