<FIRST>u f PM-Amax-Falconbridge     08-02 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Amax-Falconbridge,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>Amax Buys Canadian Metals Company</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENWICH, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Amax Inc. said today that it agreed to
purchase Falconbridge Ltd. of Toronto for $2.4 billion in cash.
   The deal is conditioned upon approval by at least two-thirds of
Falconbridge's shareholders.
   Amax said it also agreed to make an additional offer for all
untendered shares.
   Amax Chairman Allen Born said Falconbridge will fit well with
his company's metals business.
   Falconbridge is an international resource corporation that mines
and processes metals and minerals. Its major products are nickel,
ferronickel, copper and zinc. Its major operations are in Canada,
Norway and the Dominican Republic.
   Amax is a worldwide supplier of metals and energy. Its major
products are aluminium, coal, gold and molybdenum. It earned $741
million on revenue of $4.2 billion in 1988.
