   The market's unsettled showing Tuesday, when the Dow Jones
industrials fell 19.54 points, was attributed partly to concern
that the slowing of the economy might lead to something worse than
the ``soft landing'' many economists have been predicting.
   Analysts said those worries might be eased, however, by a series
of economic reports over the remainder of the week.
